Well then, let me fix something for you. How about pancakes?

80
00:08:16,746 --> 00:08:18,372
好 听起来很不错
Okay. Sounds pretty good.

81
00:08:19,165 --> 00:08:21,542
好的
Okay.

82
00:08:29,675 --> 00:08:31,844
我们找过你
We... We looked for you.

83
00:08:34,346 --> 00:08:35,639
我们去了你的公寓
We went to your apartment.

84
00:08:36,891 --> 00:08:40,393
大门敞开着 他们撕毁了你所有的书籍
The door was open and they'd torn apart all your books.

85
00:08:40,394 --> 00:08:45,107
他们打碎了那座巴西的雕塑 毁掉了整个公寓
They'd smashed that statue from Brazil. They... They destroyed everything.

86
00:08:47,280 --> 00:08:48,277
是啊
Hmm. Yeah.

87
00:08:50,529 --> 00:08:52,197
他们把我拖出去
They dragged me out.

88
00:08:52,198 --> 00:08:56,160
然后在私设法庭上审判我
And they tried me in their kangaroo court.

89
00:08:57,703 --> 00:09:01,791
戴着面具 我都看不到他们的脸
Wearing masks. I couldn't even see their faces.

90
00:09:02,625 --> 00:09:03,876
一群胆小鬼
Pussies.

91
00:09:06,295 --> 00:09:08,672
我看到了你在殖民地的照片
I saw a picture of you in the Colonies.

92
00:09:10,925 --> 00:09:11,926
我以为
I thought...

93
00:09:15,054 --> 00:09:16,389
你怎么活下来的
How did you survive that?

94
00:09:20,559 --> 00:09:22,895
一个医生还是能派上点用场
Well, a doctor's useful.

95
00:09:24,980 --> 00:09:31,696
他们叫我去照顾嬷嬷和守卫
They made me take care of the Aunts and the Guardians.

96
00:09:34,073 --> 00:09:37,576
他们囚禁了我们 杀害了我的朋友们
They kept us prisoner and killed my friends.

97
00:09:44,166 --> 00:09:46,500
但我挺过来了
But I hung on.

98
00:09:46,700 --> 00:09:49,088
能再见到你的念头支撑我咬牙走下去
With the hope that I might see you some day.

99
00:09:53,384 --> 00:09:54,468
这念头又是从何而起
What made you do that?

100
00:09:56,887 --> 00:10:00,975
我了解你 也清楚是如何抚养你长大的
I know you. And I know how I raised you.

101
00:10:02,476 --> 00:10:06,188
不管处境多么糟糕 我都坚信你一定还活着
And no matter how bad it got, I always had faith that you'd survive.

102
00:10:08,774 --> 00:10:10,359
而现在 你就在我面前
And now, here you are.

103
00:10:18,075 --> 00:10:19,368
妈 你是怎么逃出来的
How did you escape, Mom?

104
00:10:22,496 --> 00:10:23,539
是军队救了我
It was the Army.

105
00:10:25,041 --> 00:10:27,877
大概六个月前 他们解放了我所在的殖民地
They liberated my Colony about six months ago.

106
00:10:28,753 --> 00:10:31,756
- 美国军队吗 - 对
- The US Army? - Yeah.

107
00:10:33,424 --> 00:10:35,051
残余部队
What's left of 'em.

108
00:10:36,385 --> 00:10:39,429
我被送到这里后一直在找你
I got sent here and I tried to find out about you.

109
00:10:39,430 --> 00:10:42,098
但基列国封锁了阿拉斯加
But, you know, Gilead's cut Alaska off.

110
00:10:42,099 --> 00:10:45,018
没有网络 没有手机 没有新闻
No Internet, no cell, no news. So...

111
00:10:45,019 --> 00:10:48,355
我们每周能用五分钟公共电话
We have five minutes a week at the public phones.

112
00:10:48,356 --> 00:10:52,317
如其他数百万人一样 我联系了能找到的
So I called every embassy, every refugee agency I could find,

113
00:10:52,318 --> 00:10:54,152
每一个大使馆和难民署
along with millions of other people.

114
00:10:54,153 --> 00:10:58,156
但这些求助都石沉大海 所以...
But I could never get through to anyone that could help me, so I just...

115
00:10:58,157 --> 00:11:01,326
我只能下一周继续尝试
I came back the next week and tried again.

116
00:11:01,327 --> 00:11:04,372
一次又一次 我能做的只有这些
And again and again. That's all I could do.

117
00:11:07,166 --> 00:11:11,337
这个营地本应该是临时居所
This camp was, of course, meant to be temporary, but...

118
00:11:14,090 --> 00:11:17,258
是去往下一程的临时歇脚点
You know, just a way station before moving on.

119
00:11:17,259 --> 00:11:18,427
去哪里
To where?

120
00:11:19,387 --> 00:11:21,097
阿拉斯加的某处
Somewhere else in Alaska.

121
00:11:22,098 --> 00:11:23,808
夏威夷的某地
Or a spot in Hawaii.

122
00:11:24,475 --> 00:11:27,478
关岛 候补名单长着呢
Or Guam. The waitlists are long.

123
00:11:29,146 --> 00:11:32,775
夏威夷是个好地方
Hawaii would have been nice.

124
00:11:34,026 --> 00:11:36,362
不 我想尽可能长久地待在这里
No, I wanted to stay here as long as I could.

125
00:11:38,489 --> 00:11:39,782
为什么
Why?

126
00:11:40,533 --> 00:11:42,159
为了你 亲爱的
For you, sweetheart.

127
00:11:43,285 --> 00:11:44,704
我在等你
I was waiting for you and...

128
